<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-05-26T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-05-26T18:00:00-05:00" n="172" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d172">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">893.20/667: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Germany</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-05-26T19:00:00-04:00">May 26, 1938—7
                                    p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>77. In the past few days the American press has carried reports to
                                the effect that the German Government has ordered the withdrawal of
                                the German military mission from China and the stoppage of the
                                shipment of German military supplies to China. The Department would
                                welcome such information in regard to these reported developments as
                                you may be able discreetly to obtain, together with your
                                comment.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>